
	•	React functionalities: routing, buttons, cards
	•	Menu bar with route integration
	•	Auto deploy via Netlify with free hosting
	•	Everything explained clearly for recruiters or contributors

⸻

Sai Vinay’s Developer Portfolio

This is my personal developer portfolio built using React.js and Tailwind CSS. It highlights my technical skills, projects, and development experience. The site is optimized for performance, responsive on all devices, and hosted with free auto-deploy via Netlify.

⸻

Live Website

Visit Portfolio
(Replace with your actual Netlify URL)

⸻

Features & Functionalities

React Usage Highlights
	•	React Router DOM:
	•	Multi-page navigation using react-router-dom
	•	Dynamic routing for About, Projects, Contact, etc.
	•	Example:

<Routes>
  <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
  <Route path="/projects" element={<Projects />} />
  <Route path="/contact" element={<Contact />} />
</Routes>


	•	Menu Bar Navigation:
	•	Responsive menu bar with route-based navigation
	•	Active link highlighting
	•	Reusable Buttons:
	•	Styled with Tailwind CSS and props-based customization
	•	Clickable buttons for GitHub links, project demos, and resume download
	•	Card Components:
	•	Dynamic project cards with hover animation and clickable actions
	•	Cards include:
	•	Project title, tech stack, short description, and links
	•	Example:

<ProjectCard
  title="AI Chatbot"
  techStack="React, Node.js, OpenAI API"
  link="https://github.com/SaiVinay023/ai-chatbot"
/>



⸻

Tech Stack
	•	Frontend: React.js, Tailwind CSS, Vite, Framer Motion
	•	Routing: react-router-dom
	•	Animation: Framer Motion
	•	Tooling: VS Code, Prettier, ESLint
	•	Version Control: Git & GitHub
	•	Deployment: Netlify (auto-deploy from GitHub)

⸻

Deployment on Netlify (Free & Auto Deploy)
	1.	Push code to a GitHub repository
	2.	Connect repo to Netlify
	3.	Build Command: npm run build
	4.	Publish directory: dist/
	5.	Auto-deployment is triggered on every commit to main branch

⸻

Install & Run Locally

git clone https://github.com/SaiVinay023/portfolio.git
cd portfolio
npm install
npm run dev

Open http://localhost:5173 to view in browser.

